descriptionMarkdown:
MegaCity to Space is a blueprint series that I have specifically modified for the Space Age DLC ,you need to have the DLC in order to use this blueprint. 
You can view the original version here: https://www.factorio.school/view/-NVIYNeGyxfJfkfz3MGF.

This series includes modular rails and elevated bridges that can be freely combined to quickly create a large base. The trains feature the new interrupt system and capacity display, and they are programmed to prioritize high-demand areas. It is intended for use roughly after you launch your first rocket into space—at which point, if you are aiming to complete the achievements, your technology might still be limited to red belts and T2 assemblers.

All the blueprints avoid using mixed underground belt techniques, making upgrades and replacements very convenient. Additionally, the blueprint includes a basic parameterized train, which allows you to easily swap out any recipe to accommodate other mods. I must note that I am not entirely certain if the factory layout design is optimal, as my primary focus was on aesthetics.

P.S. If you have any issues while using it, check out this video: https://www.twitch.tv/videos/2377549156
the blueprints should work like that way~

Please report any errors, as there might be many bugs. Thank you!(,, ･∀･)ﾉ゛
